headline: Havana, a ghost town battered by shortages and US threats
description: 'Cuba, an island adrift' (1/3) In the small socialist country, US pressure for regime change has reached its peak since the kidnapping of Venezuelan leader Nicolas Maduro on January 3. Daily life has become a nightmare, and public discourse is more closely monitored than ever.

headline: Trump battles Minneapolis shooting fallout as agents put on leave
Springsteen dedicates fiery ode to the people of Minneapolis
Escaped Syrian detainees recount chaos after Kurdish forces withdraw
description: The security handover of prisons and detention camps from the Kurdish-led Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) to the authorities in Damascus took place amid total confusion, allowing several dozen prisoners to escape. Each side has blamed the other for the incident.

headline: John Bolton: 'Toppling the Iranian regime is the most effective way to remove the terrorist threat the West has faced'
description: The former US national security adviser argues, in an op-ed for Le Monde, that the EU stands out for its passivity in the face of the Islamic Republic, while that dictatorship carries out assassinations of dissidents in Europe, supports international terrorism and poses a nuclear threat.

headline: French senate adopts a bill to ease the return of colonial-era artifacts to their countries of origin
description: The new legislation aims to broaden the restitution of colonial-era assets, introducing clear criteria and a transparent process for handling requests from the countries involved.

headline: Charles Kushner, Trump's man in Paris
description: The 71-year-old US ambassador, who took up his post in May 2025, is the father of Jared Kushner, Donald Trump's son-in-law and envoy to the Middle East. Like his son, he is known for his unorthodox methods and does not hesitate to interfere in France's domestic affairs.

Work-related cancers remain a blind spot in France's public health system
description: A study conducted by doctors and occupational sociologists at the Avignon Hospital Center on over 500 lymphoma patients found there was a 'massive underestimation' of work-related cancers in France.

headline: How India and the EU created a common market to counter Trump
description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and representatives of the European Union concluded a trade agreement on January 27, after nearly 20 years of intermittent negotiations, opening up a market of nearly two billion people.

headline: 2026 FIFA World Cup: Calls for boycott emerge to bring Trump 'to his senses'
description: The US president's desire to claim Greenland has prompted political figures to raise the possibility of national football teams withdrawing.
